This reverts commit 8888798f95804c9359a633e850b5406ea928b593.

Merge branch 'py-stable-abi2'

  Switch to SWIG_Py_DECREF instead of Py_Decref
  Show ABI version in CI job name

  Unused parameter warning fix in SWIG_Python_TypeError

  configure.ac python versions update

  Py_DECREF -> Py_DecRef for stable ABI compliance
  Py_IncRef casts

  Py_INCREF -> Py_IncRef for stable ABI compliance

  minor enhancement in changes file

	CHANGES.current

Add abi3audit information for Python stable ABI

Use PyObject_Free instead of deprecated macros

Python 3.10 comments the macros PyObject_Del and PyObject_DEL as deprecated
Don't run abi3audit on builtin test

Strict Python stable abi conformance fix for PyUnicode_GetLength

PyUnicode_GetLength is officially documented as being in the stable abi
from python-3.7 onwards. It is is actually available in the Python
headers when compiling with Py_LIMITED_API set to 0x03030000 (python-3.3)
and later. This change ensures it is only used when Py_LIMITED_API is
set to 0x03070000 (python-3.7) and later for strict conformance.
Don't use abi3audit if not installed
Unused parameter warning fix in SWIG_Python_TypeError

Add PY_ABI_VER for testing Python stable ABI using abi3audit

For example to check the stable ABI version 3.4:
  make check-python-examples check-python-test-suite PY_ABI_VER=3.4

configure.ac python versions update

Don't look for unsupported python-3.2 version.
Look for future versions 3.13-3.15 as well as 3.11 and 3.12

Also look for abi3audit

Fix elision of comma before ##__VARARGS__

We document this as supported but it seems to have not worked since
before 2009.
